      • createStream

        protected abstract InputStream createStream(long startPos,
                                            long endPos)
                                     throws IOException
        Open a new stream reading a range. When endPos > content length, the returned stream should read till the last valid byte of the input. The behaviour is undefined when (startPos < 0), (startPos >= content length), or (endPos <= 0).
        Parameters:
        startPos - start position in bytes (inclusive)
        endPos - end position in bytes (exclusive)
        Returns:
        a new InputStream
        Throws:
        IOException - when a non-Alluxio error occurs
